nt of its benefits and risks. [Data: Entities (2376), Relationships (2757)]\n\n## SSRIs as a class of antidepressants\n\nSelective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs), including Paroxetine and Sertraline, are a class of antidepressants widely used for treating depression and anxiety. They work by increasing serotonin levels in the brain, which helps improve mood and reduce anxiety. SSRIs are preferred over other antidepressants due to their relatively mild side effect profile and lower risk of dependency. [Data: Entities (2094), Relationships (2373, 2374)]\n\n## Combination therapy for complex conditions\n\nCombination therapy, such as using Pimozide with Sertraline, is a common approach for treating complex psychiatric conditions like Tourette syndrome and OCD. This strategy leverages the complementary mechanisms of different drugs to enhance overall treatment efficacy. However, it also requires careful management to mitigate potential side effects and drug interactions. [Data: Relationships (2757)]", "# Antipsychotic Medications and Their Therapeutic Applications\n\nThis community centers around various antipsychotic medications and their applications in treating conditions such as obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) and Tourette syndrome. Key entities include 氟哌啶醇 (Haloperidol), 利培酮 (Risperidone), 喹硫平 (Quetiapine), and 哌迷清 (Pimozide), which are interconnected through their therapeutic uses and mechanisms of action. The relationships highlight their efficacy in treating specific conditions and their potential side effects, emphasizing their clinical significance.\n\n## 氟哌啶醇 as a key antipsychotic medication\n\n氟哌啶醇 (Haloperidol) is a prominent antipsychotic medication used to enhance the treatment efficacy of obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD). Its high degree of connectivity in the community underscores its importance in clinical applications. The medication is often used in combination with other drugs, such as 肌苷 (Inosine) and 氯硝地泮 (Clonazepam), to improve t